        <h1><marquee height="45">Tomato Rice</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup basmati rice</li>
            <li>3 large tomatoes, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 large onion, thinly sliced</li>
            <li>1/4 cup peanuts</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon mustard seeds</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>1 bay leaf</li>
            <li>1 cinnamon stick</li>
            <li>2-3 cloves</li>
            <li>2 cups water</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>vegetarian</li>
            <li>rice</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
    

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Rinse the basmati rice under cold water until the water runs clear. Soak it in water for 30 minutes, then drain.</li>
            <li>In a large pot, heat vegetable oil over medium heat. Add mustard seeds, cumin seeds, bay leaf, cinnamon stick, and cloves. Sauté for a minute until the seeds splutter.</li>
            <li>Add sliced onions and cook until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add peanuts and sauté until they are lightly roasted.</li>
            <li>Add chopped tomatoes and cook until they are soft and the oil separates from the masala.</li>
            <li>Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well.</li>
            <li>Add soaked and drained basmati rice. Stir well to coat the rice with the tomato masala.</li>
            <li>Pour in water and bring the mixture to a boil. Reduce the heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15-20 minutes or until the rice is cooked and the water is absorbed.</li>
            <li>Remove the pot from heat and let it sit, covered, for 5 minutes. Fluff the rice with a fork.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves.</li>
            <li>Serve hot as a delicious Tomato Rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Tomato Rice!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
